Identifying problems and issues. Describing problems. Gathering information necessary for solving problems. Analysing problems. Making suggestions for solving problems. The methods of problem-based learning are applied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to give students the opportunity to solve a case study representing an issue or problem prevalent at a social or rehabilitation institution. The students have to utilize the knowledge and skills they have obtained throughout the various courses they have passed and establish connections between theory and practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) analyse problems occurring at an organisation; 2) apply appropriate principles and methods for solving problems; 3) make use of obtained knowledge and skills for solving problems; 4) analyse and make conclusions and suggestions for solving problems.
